# Public display (`/display/[roomCode]`)

The TV display is a **read-only fullscreen kiosk**. It never hosts controls, forms, or host/player affordances.

## Non-negotiables

1. **Read-only** — Socket state in, pixels out. No buttons, links, inputs, or editable UI.
2. **Fullscreen kiosk** — Auto-request fullscreen on load; re-enter after exit or tab focus. No "exit fullscreen" affordance.
3. **Bar-TV legibility** — Every label, score, guess, tile, and status indicator must be readable from across a bar. When in doubt, go larger and higher contrast.
4. **No truncation** — Prefer wrap, scale down the board, or paginate. Never clip text the audience needs.
5. **Display ≠ host** — Do not reuse host badges, compact typography, or `MusicBackdrop`. Use `display-stage` / TV variants only.

## Tile hierarchy (lyric board)

| State | Treatment |
|-------|-----------|
| Hidden blank | Gold pill + letter count |
| Pre-revealed | Dark pill, same size as blanks, white text |
| Player-revealed | Bright gold pill + pop animation |
| Punctuation | White glow, no box |

All tile types share `--tv-scale` sizing; pre-revealed must never be smaller than blanks.

## Typography floor (TV)

- Body base: `clamp(20px, 1.35vw, 26px)` on `.display-stage`
- Round title: `text-5xl+`, phase: `text-2xl+`
- Sidebar panel titles: `text-2xl` uppercase
- Leaderboard row: `text-2xl` name, `text-3xl` score
- Live feed hero guess: `text-3xl+`
- Connection status: spelled out (`LIVE` / `OFFLINE`), not a dot alone

## Layout

- Fixed `inset-0`, `overflow-hidden`, no page scroll
- Board scales to fit; long songs use ≤2 lyric lines per display row
- Sidebar ~380px; three panels: Puzzle, Leaderboard, Live Feed
